,Not Recommended,556230,28315076,"Posted: 11 December, 2016",all,Punkers,"In it's current state the game is playable and fairly entertaining.  However, there is still a lot of work to do before calling this rock crawling ""simulator' a finished product.My video on it - caution - lots of swearingThe first true annoyance is the vehicle audio.  It's awful, simply awful.  It's super loud, sounds like the recording mic was directly in the engine bay of a semi-truck.  It sounds nothing like what you'd expect from whatever vehicle you're using in game.The very next, second, annoyance you'll find is with the camera.  I swear the camera in ""orbit"" mode is literally trying to get you killed.  It's actually worse than the obit cam from BeamNG, which is saying a lot.Physics model seems ok.  However, the suspension set up, amount of grip, and power are completely out of wack.  The suspension is way too stiff.  Vehicles bounce all over the place because of this.  Tire grip is greatly exaggerated, so much so that you can actually flip the vehicle back on it's wheels in some roll-over situations.  Lastly, now I don't think I've ever said this before, but the power these vehicles put to the wheels is just way too much.  290hp, sure, but the vehicles all feel like they're pushing well over 1000 ft lbs of tourqe,  Wheelies are cool on a strip of pavement, but not when you're precariously positioned on a rock.Game crashes occasionally.The game has tons of potential, though, don't get me wrong.  It's fun, too.  But I just can't recommend the game in it's current state for $11 cdn."
